  "title": "Deploying and Using Jenkins in Kubernetes",
  "type": "lab",
  "description": "This experiment explains how to deploy Jenkins in Kubernetes, initialize it, create a simple pipeline, and implement a dynamic slave through Kubernetes. Jenkins is open-source software used for automating a variety of tasks, including building, testing, and deploying software. It comes with different features such as open-source and free, multi-platform support, Master-slave distributed architecture, easy installation and configuration, web visual configuration management page, and rich plug-in resources. For easier deployment, Docker deployment is used, and Kubernetes orchestration is used. Users will create a PVC for Jenkins, create Jenkins-role and authorize it, and then deploy the Jenkins application.",
